<paragraph id="644FD64944D260B177C713745FDF7632" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(Green in 
<bibRefCitation id="61082FBD7A6840B8F168C1865FD17A17" author="Hitchcock, AG" journalOrPublisher="Botany Letters" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="https://bibdigital.rjb.csic.es/medias/1b/d4/fd/65/1bd4fd65-6b60-4307-80b2-493516e8cf25/files/Int_Bot_Congr_1930_Prop_Brit.pdf" refId="B40" refString="Hitchcock, AG, Green, ML, 1929. Standard-species of Linnean genera of Phanerogamae (1753-54). International Botanical Congress Cambridge (England), 1930, Nomenclature. Proposals by British botanists. Printed under the authority of H.M.S.O. by Wyman &amp; Sons, London, 110-199. https://bibdigital.rjb.csic.es/medias/1b/d4/fd/65/1bd4fd65-6b60-4307-80b2-493516e8cf25/files/Int_Bot_Congr_1930_Prop_Brit.pdf" title="Standard-species of Linnean genera of Phanerogamae (1753 - 54). International Botanical Congress Cambridge (England), 1930, Nomenclature. Proposals by British botanists. Printed under the authority of H. M. S. O. by Wyman &amp; Sons, London, 110 - 199." url="https://bibdigital.rjb.csic.es/medias/1b/d4/fd/65/1bd4fd65-6b60-4307-80b2-493516e8cf25/files/Int_Bot_Congr_1930_Prop_Brit.pdf" year="1929">Hitchcock and Green 1929</bibRefCitation>
: 177): 
<taxonomicName id="03E34179707D00BF7915114C93E9AAA3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Scorzonera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Scorzonera humilis" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis id="64D77F7C841BDB7D288183BE47B71D3D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Scorzonera humilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="17DF0C9386B13932FABB2027A2C92898" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="52D10161255082850CDE8E57139F2D66" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B67002C461A6A5C44A2A560819B0978" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="12E4C379018841A507ECBAD2CD317603" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Scorzonera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Scorzonera" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87B920713FF44BE4B6A6AA7399164D58" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Scorzonera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this revised sense as a monophyletic genus includes four larger clades, the 
<taxonomicName id="3FBE42DC7595038A8B21CA98EB23C594" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Scorzonera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Scorzonera" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DA6BBE624F4D6282B083A8A57D9BCB0E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Scorzonera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.str. clade (3 spp.), 
<taxonomicName id="65A73F835A70260F847D650B66927F5E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Scorzonera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Scorzonera albicaulis" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albicaulis">
<emphasis id="84AF427C2BC58F8789083DEB04B2B0A2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Scorzonera albicaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade (~17 spp.), 
<taxonomicName id="5D4083997409E7BEC1BAA451857BBECF" authority="Lipsch., 1935 (DC.)" authorityName="Lipsch., 1935 (DC.)" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Podospermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Podospermum" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D564E00D83A48F7B6641A4D38A147E12" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Podospermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade (~20 spp.) and 
<taxonomicName id="3DA485F42F242221FC6D536DEB9C5666" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Scorzonera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Scorzonera purpurea" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpurea">
<emphasis id="ED8615141DCEBBAEACBE433D0E2CB925" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Scorzonera purpurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade (2 spp.). In addition, it includes a few, so far somewhat isolated species (
<taxonomicName id="0F520FF37582339CA10DC211A82616B7" family="Asteraceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. rupicola" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="rupicola">
<emphasis id="433C701A3D68DB5028BEDBAE439C189B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. rupicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DDF686B39A18E206BD7521160A197A43" family="Asteraceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. renzii" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="renzii">
<emphasis id="35B2BE27D368B6CE78A8E67D531F52C5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. renzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B33A13C02668FFB390E459E2C80C3ECD" family="Asteraceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. angustifolia" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="angustifolia">
<emphasis id="61C857100792B06B5A563835218CA3AE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. angustifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The genus in this cricumscription still shows considerable variation. Our analysis is insufficient with respect to a revision of the elaborated infrageneric classifications of previous authors. We therefore refer here to the clades of our trees.
</paragraph>
